The '''Calymmian Period''' (from [[Greek language|Greek]] κάλυμμα ''(kálymma)'', meaning "cover") is the first [[geologic]] [[geologic period|period]] in the [[Mesoproterozoic]] [[Era (geology)|Era]] and lasted from {{Period start|Calymmian}} [[annum|Mya]] to {{Period start|Ectasian}} Mya (million years ago). Instead of being based on [[stratigraphy]], these dates are defined [[Absolute dating|chronometrically]].

The period is characterised by expansion of existing [[platform cover]]s, or by new [[continental shelf|platform]]s on recently [[craton]]ized [[Basement (geology)|basement]]s.

The [[supercontinent]] [[Columbia (supercontinent)|Columbia]] broke up during the Calymmian some 1500 Mya.

