{{short description|A cabled-based observatory system below the surface of Monterey Bay}} '''Monterey Accelerated Research System''' ('''MARS''') is a [[Wire rope|cabled]]-based observatory system below the surface of [[Monterey Bay]], developed and managed by the [[Monterey Bay Aquarium Research Institute]].<ref>[http://www.mbari.org/mars MARS home page]</ref> The system, operational since November 10, 2008, incorporates a {{convert|52|km|mi|abbr=on}} undersea cable that carries data and power to [[benthic]] instrument nodes, [[AUV]]s, and various [[benthic]] and [[Mooring (oceanography)|moored instrumentation]].
